Text: Short and sweet blog for the week.
What we achieved.
We accomplished most of the goals we needed to finish this week.
This included finalising the layout of our end screen design and figuring out how to connect everything together.
We also got our second focus group out of the way, although we may need to follow up with two people because they were unavailable.
I achieved all the goals I set out from last week, which was contributing to each aspect of the project, setting up a trello account, and teaching some of my team mates the code I had worked on.
The good.
I felt like this was our best week as a team, we've hit a good stride in terms of how we work and understand each other.
Kiki had an exam to study for, so she took two days off to prepare.
We used most of the days to code on what we had started, so we were able to keep up with the productivity.
Kiki did most of the work for the focus group so she has managed to contribute to the team despite being busy.
Our second focus group went much better than our first one.
We went on Zoom during the day to test the zoom link and all the functions we wanted to use.
We also had a practice run through what we were going to say.
This extra practice benefited our focus group, and we managed to finish earlier than expected.
Tzu - Rara spoke for half of the focus group, so she has been working hard on practising her speaking skills.
Susu has been spending a lot of time on the Shiny design.
It has been fun working with people who are motivated and hard working!.
Things to improve on as a team.
We possibly could have gotten a bit more coding time in on Friday, but it was a good week overall.
Things I could do better.
IÂ  had the task of leading the Friday presentation and I believe it went smoothly.
I could have doneÂ  better organising what I was going to say.
It was also tricky using zoom while in front of people, as I almost completely forgot there were people in the room and realised I may have been talking at the screen for most of it!.
Overall, the week went well and it was satisfying addressing the issues I was concerned about last week.
Especially being able to go through the work I had done with the team.
It seems my teammates have appreciated any work I've done, so I may have been overthinking last week.
Goals for next week.
Finish our shiny app, clean up the functions we are using and get the presentation out the way!.
General thoughts.

I was having a chat with some of my teammates and I have realised that the short time frame for these projects does benefit people who are able to pick things up faster, or have less commitments outside the project.
This could be an issue as people who lack the appropriate time to soak up new ideas and skills will not gain as much as people who have more free time or learn faster.
Although I am confident that everyone will benefit from these projects, I am a little concerned that some people could feel left behind.
I am aware that these issues should be brought up by the individuals with these concerns, but I also know that some people might be shy asking for help.

Could there be extra opportunities for growth that we could run outside of class?For example, could we run through mini projects (1-2 hours) that go through working on a project using a specific language?
Could students run these sessions?
Should we run CTF's or some other beginner hacking competitions with the signal group?
These ideas might have been done in the past, so no worries if they have been tried and failed!.I apologise if my writing isn't very sharp today, I left it a little late in the day for it.
Carpe Diem.
Overall
